- The cardil hinge teeth was reduced considerably, from both points (the hole got bigger, but the teeth also got significantly thinner)

After 1 tumble:
- It is very interesting to me that, as the shell gets sanded, it reveals more of its darker gray interior. This confirms my assumptions that this particular species of Glycymeris is not the one we found.
